title: Mystic Pizza
cast: Annabeth Gish, Julia Roberts, Lili Taylor, Vincent D'Onofrio, William R. Moses, Adam Storke, Conchata Ferrell, Joanna Merlin, Porscha Radcliffe, John Fiore
summary: In this quirky linchpin of 1980s cinema, reality intrudes on the plans of three teens who share their dreams while slinging hash at a pizzeria.

title: Khumba
cast: Jake T. Austin, Liam Neeson, Steve Buscemi, AnnaSophia Robb, Laurence Fishburne, Greg Ellis, Richard E. Grant, Catherine Tate, Anika Noni Rose, Loretta Devine

title: Barton Fink
cast: John Turturro, John Goodman, Judy Davis, Michael Lerner, John Mahoney, Tony Shalhoub, Jon Polito, Steve Buscemi, David Warrilow, Richard Portnow
summary: When Hollywood taps him to pen a movie script, an idealistic playwright develops severe writer's block and gets tangled up in a murder investigation.

title: Parting Glances
cast: Richard Ganoung, John Bolger, Steve Buscemi, Adam Nathan, Kathy Kinney, Patrick Tull, Yolande Bavan, Andre Morgan
summary: Upwardly mobile Robert accepts a long-term assignment in Africa that will inevitably strain his relationship with his lover, Michael.

title: Desperado
cast: Antonio Banderas, Salma Hayek, Joaquim de Almeida, Cheech Marin, Steve Buscemi, Carlos Gómez, Quentin Tarantino, Tito Larriva, Angel Aviles, Danny Trejo
summary: This south-of-the-border action flick picks up where the 1992 indie hit El Mariachi left off. Seeking revenge for the killing of his girlfriend, El Mariachi goes in search of the seedy drug lord responsible -- and a showdown ensues.

title: 28 Days
cast: Sandra Bullock, Viggo Mortensen, Dominic West, Elizabeth Perkins, Azura Skye, Steve Buscemi, Alan Tudyk, Mike O'Malley, Marianne Jean-Baptiste, Reni Santoni
summary: After her drunken antics ruin her sister's wedding and result in major property damage, journalist Gwen Cummings enters rehab, where she runs afoul of the program director -- and soon meets a fellow resident who changes her outlook.

title: Airheads
cast: Brendan Fraser, Steve Buscemi, Adam Sandler, Chris Farley, Michael McKean, Judd Nelson, Ernie Hudson, Amy Locane, Nina Siemaszko, Marshall Bell
summary: The Lone Rangers have heavy-metal aspirations and a single demo tape that they can't get anyone to play. The solution: Hijack a radio station and hold the deejays hostage until they agree to broadcast the band's tape.

title: Tales from the Darkside: The Movie
cast: Deborah Harry, Matthew Lawrence, Christian Slater, Steve Buscemi, Donald Van Horn, Julianne Moore, James Remar, Rae Dawn Chong, Robert Klein, David Johansen
summary: In this feature spinoff of the creepy television anthology, psycho chef Betty plans to cook a little boy. The crafty tyke, however, stalls the violence by distracting Betty with three tales of terror.

title: Spy Kids 2: The Island of Lost Dreams
cast: Antonio Banderas, Carla Gugino, Alexa Vega, Daryl Sabara, Steve Buscemi, Mike Judge, Danny Trejo, Cheech Marin, Matt O'Leary, Emily Osment
summary: In this sequel to the hit sci-fi family adventure, spy kids Carmen and and Juni Cortez team up with two other pint-size secret agents, Gary and Gerti Giggles. The foursome travels to a mysterious island to save the world from an evil scientist.

title: Love in the Time of Money
cast: Vera Farmiga, Domenick Lombardozzi, Jill Hennessy, Malcolm Gets, Steve Buscemi, Rosario Dawson, Adrian Grenier, Carol Kane, Michael Imperioli, Nahanni Johnstone
summary: Love is a battlefield for several New York City dwellers: a prostitute and her trick; an artist and a receptionist he meets; a woman married to an unhappy art dealer with a secret; and a psychic out to save a man's life.

title: Things to Do in Denver When You're Dead
cast: Andy Garcia, Christopher Lloyd, William Forsythe, Bill Nunn, Treat Williams, Jack Warden, Steve Buscemi, Fairuza Balk, Gabrielle Anwar, Christopher Walken
summary: Former hoodlum Jimmy the Saint assembles his old gang of five guys for what starts off as a simple assignment handed down from "The Man With a Plan." But things go awry fast -- and they all might end up dead.

title: John Rabe

summary: Florian Gallenberger directs this gripping drama about John Rabe (Ulrich Tukur), a German businessman living in Nanking, China, who in 1937 used his Nazi party affiliation to save some 200,000 Chinese civilians from slaughter at the hands of the Japanese army. As Rabe labors to establish an official safety zone to shelter the innocent, he forms an unlikely friendship with an American doctor (Steve Buscemi). Anne Consigny and Daniel Brühl co-star.

title: Fargo
cast: Frances McDormand, William H. Macy, Steve Buscemi, Peter Stormare, Harve Presnell, John Carroll Lynch, Kristin Rudrüd, Larry Brandenburg, Steve Park, Cliff Rakerd
summary: Police chief Marge Gunderson -- a serious sleuth who's sharper than her folksy accent suggests -- is hot on the trail of a Minneapolis car dealer conspiring with two kidnappers to snatch his wife so he can pocket part of the hefty ransom.

title: King of New York
cast: Christopher Walken, David Caruso, Laurence Fishburne, Victor Argo, Wesley Snipes, Janet Julian, Joey Chin, Giancarlo Esposito, Paul Calderon, Steve Buscemi

title: Escape from L.A.
cast: Kurt Russell, Steve Buscemi, Peter Fonda, Cliff Robertson, Valeria Golino, Stacy Keach, Pam Grier, Bruce Campbell, Georges Corraface, Michelle Forbes
summary: Kurt Russell reprises his role as antihero Snake Plissken. This time, a cataclysmic temblor hits Los Angeles, turning it into an island. The president (Cliff Robertson) views the quake as a sign from above, expels Los Angeles from the country and makes it a penal colony for those found guilty of moral crimes. When his daughter, part of a resistance movement, steals the control unit for a doomsday weapon, Snake again gets tapped to save the day.

title: The Chosen One
cast: Steve Buscemi, Rob Schneider, Holland Taylor, Peter Riegert, George Dzundza, Samantha Smith, Marcus Giamatti, Carolina Gómez, Mary Decaro
summary: When beaten-down car salesman Paul (Rob Schneider) decides that his life is meaningless, fate intervenes to put a new spin on things: A mysterious band of strangers appears at his door to tell him he's got it all wrong. In fact, the entire world has been thrown out of balance, and they're there seeking the Chosen One -- the one soul who can set the universe right. With no better plan, Paul begins keeping an eye out for his moment of destiny.

title: Glick Doesn't Do Red Carpet: Jiminy Glick at the Independent Spirit Awards
cast: Martin Short, Rainn Wilson, Dennis Hopper, Maria Bello, Ellen Page, Steve Buscemi, Ivan Reitman, Jason Reitman, John Waters, Allison Janney
summary: Martin Short reprises his role as Jiminy Glick -- the overweight celebrity interviewer who asks only irreverent and irrelevant questions -- at the Netflix Home Suite Home stop on the red carpet at the 2008 Independent Spirit Awards. He gets couch time with host Rainn Wilson, Maria Bello, Ellen Page, Dennis Hopper, Steve Buscemi, Ed Begley Jr. and more, who take Glick's insults all in stride. Plenty of pillow fighting, donut munching and inappropriateness abound.

title: Coffee and Cigarettes
cast: Bill Murray, Tom Waits, Roberto Benigni, Steven Wright, Joie Lee, Cinque Lee, Steve Buscemi, Iggy Pop, Joseph Rigano, Vinny Vella
summary: Jim Jarmusch's quirky ensemble comedy is presented as a series of vignettes that all revolve around discussions held over coffee and cigarettes.

title: Trees Lounge
cast: Steve Buscemi, Mark Boone Junior, Chloë Sevigny, Michael Buscemi, Anthony LaPaglia, Elizabeth Bracco, Carol Kane, Bronson Dudley, John Ventimiglia, Steven Randazzo
summary: A shiftless barfly spends all his time at the neighborhood watering hole, in good company as he deadens the pain of his unfortunate life choices.

title: Domestic Disturbance

summary: A recovering alcoholic is skeptical of his son's claim that his new stepfather is a killer -- but soon begins to sense the boy is telling the truth.

title: Mr. Deeds

title: The Swan Princess

title: A Fish Called Wanda

summary: A crooked foursome commits the heist of the century and is about to get away with it until the London police arrests one of them. Can the three on the lam persuade their comrade's lawyer to reveal the stolen loot's location?

title: George of the Jungle 2
cast: Chris Showerman, Julie Benz, Angus T. Jones, Thomas Haden Church, Christina Pickles, John Cleese, Michael Clarke Duncan, John Kassir, Kevin Greutert, Keith Scott
summary: Having married the beautiful Ursula and fathered a child, clumsy ape-man George is perfectly content. But soon, all is not well in George's jungle kingdom as Really Mean Lion challenges him for the throne and his mother-in-law schemes against him.

title: Mickey's House of Villains
cast: Wayne Allwine, Tony Anselmo, Jeff Bennett, Susanne Blakeslee, Corey Burton, Pat Carroll, John Cleese, Jim Cummings, Bill Farmer, John Fiedler
director: Jamie Mitchell, Tony Craig, Roberts Gannaway, Mike Moon, Rick Schneider-Calabash

title: Mickey's Magical Christmas: Snowed in at the House of Mickey Mouse
cast: Wayne Allwine, Tony Anselmo, John Cleese, Jodi Benson, Bill Farmer, Paige O'Hara
summary: When a huge snowstorm leaves everyone stranded at the House of Mouse, Mickey and his guests, including Pooh, Piglet, Belle, Snow White, Ariel and many more, break out the cookies and hot chocolate to help Donald Duck regain his holiday spirit.

title: A Liar's Autobiography: The Untrue Story of Monty Python's Graham Chapman
cast: Graham Chapman, John Cleese, Terry Gilliam, Terry Jones, Michael Palin, Eric Idle, Cameron Diaz, Carol Cleveland, Stephen Fry, Diana Kent
director: Jeff Simpson, Bill Jones, Benjamin Timlett
summary: Through a variety of animation styles, this unconventional biopic tells the extraordinary and utterly inaccurate story behind late Monty Python member Graham Chapman, who recorded passages from his autobiography shortly before his death in 1989.

title: Monty Python's The Meaning of Life
cast: Graham Chapman, John Cleese, Terry Gilliam, Eric Idle, Terry Jones, Michael Palin, Carol Cleveland, Simon Jones, Patricia Quinn
summary: The no-holds-barred Pythons explore the various facets of life -- from procreation to the clang of a death knell -- in their typical irreverent fashion. Darker and more disturbing than other Monty Python fare, the film follows a sketch comedy format.

title: Graham Chapman: Anatomy of a Liar
cast: Graham Chapman, John Cleese, Terry Gilliam, Terry Jones, Michael Palin
director: Bill Jones, Jeff Simpson, Benjamin Timlett
summary: The extraordinary story behind the film, A Liar's Autobiography, based on the memoir of the late Monty Python member, Graham Chapman. Illustrating how the film brings the comedy legend to life through animation and recently discovered recordings.

title: Fawlty Towers

summary: Haughty, misadventure-prone Basil Fawlty and his bossy wife, Sybil, try to raise the profile of their "English Riviera" operation -- the Fawlty Towers Hotel -- but never-ending misunderstandings arise, leading to constant farcical lunacy.

title: Charlie's Angels: Full Throttle
cast: Cameron Diaz, Drew Barrymore, Lucy Liu, Bernie Mac, Crispin Glover, Justin Theroux, Robert Patrick, Demi Moore, Rodrigo Santoro, Shia LaBeouf, Matt LeBlanc, Luke Wilson, John Cleese, Ja'Net DuBois, Robert Forster

title: The Out-of-Towners

summary: Empty-nesters Henry and Nancy Clark hit New York for a job interview and with high hopes of reviving their extremely stale relationship.

title: The Original Kings of Comedy

summary: Director Spike Lee documents the final night of the popular comedy tour featuring four black funnymen -- Steve Harvey, Cedric the Entertainer, D.L. Hughley and Bernie Mac -- who do their part to revive stand-up comedy's glory days.

title: Ride

title: A Haunted House
cast: Marlon Wayans, Marlene Forte, Essence Atkins, David Koechner, Dave Sheridan, Nick Swardson, Alanna Ubach, Andrew Daly, Cedric the Entertainer, Affion Crockett
summary: In this spoof of horror films like Paranormal Activity, Marlon Wayans stars as an immature guy who's frightened when he learns the girlfriend who just moved in with him has been possessed by a demonic spirit.

title: Man of the House
cast: Tommy Lee Jones, Cedric the Entertainer, Christina Milian, Paula Garcés, Monica Keena, Vanessa Ferlito, Kelli Garner, Anne Archer, Brian Van Holt, Shea Whigham
summary: Texas Ranger Roland Sharp finds himself college bound when he's tapped to protect a boisterous group of University of Texas cheerleaders who happen to be the only witnesses to a federal snitch's murder.

title: DreamWorks Happy Holidays from Madagascar
cast: Tom McGrath, Chris Miller, Christopher Knights, John DiMaggio, Ben Stiller, Chris Rock, David Schwimmer, Jada Pinkett Smith, Cedric the Entertainer, Andy Richter
summary: There's no shortage of love on Valentine's Day when King Julian dons an alluring perfume with magical powers. Then, with Christmas in the air, Private the penguin gets stuck in a stocking and needs help from his pals to get out.

title: Grassroots
cast: Jason Biggs, Joel David Moore, Lauren Ambrose, Cedric the Entertainer, Tom Arnold, Cobie Smulders, Todd Stashwick, Emily Bergl, D.C. Pierson, Michael Nardelli
summary: Based on a true story, this inspiring comedy tells the tale of unemployed writer Phil Campbell, who's roped into helping his quirky friend Grant run for Seattle city council. Surprisingly, Grant's passion for mass transit may win him the election.

title: All's Faire in Love
cast: Christina Ricci, Owen Benjamin, Ann-Margret, Matthew Lillard, Cedric the Entertainer, Louise Griffiths, Sandra Taylor, Martin Klebba, Dave Sheridan, Bill Engvall
summary: Sparks fly when college football standout Will and beguiling investment banker Kate -- both temporarily working as costumed actors in a Renaissance Faire -- join forces to thwart a rival theater group from commandeering the Faire's main stage.

title: Barbershop
cast: Ice Cube, Anthony Anderson, Cedric the Entertainer, Sean Patrick Thomas, Eve, Troy Garity, Michael Ealy, Leonard Earl Howze, Keith David, Jazsmin Lewis
summary: A $50,000 reward offer for information about a recent heist sends a barbershop on Chicago's south side, already a hub of rumors, into a frenzy.

title: Barbershop 2: Back in Business
cast: Ice Cube, Cedric the Entertainer, Sean Patrick Thomas, Eve, Michael Ealy, Leonard Earl Howze, Harry Lennix, Robert Wisdom, Queen Latifah, Troy Garity
summary: When a glitzy, high-class hair salon opens across the street, barbershop owner Calvin finds his mom-and-pop business threatened in this comic sequel.

title: A Haunted House 2
cast: Marlon Wayans, Jaime Pressly, Essence Atkins, Gabriel Iglesias, Cedric the Entertainer, Missi Pyle, Ashley Rickards, Affion Crockett, Steele Stebbins, Rick Overton, Hayes MacArthur, Dave Sheridan
summary: Marlon Wayans returns in this spoofy sequel as the grieving Malcolm, who's trying to move on after his girlfriend's untimely tragic death.

title: The Fox and the Hound 2
cast: Reba McEntire, Patrick Swayze, Jonah Bobo, Harrison Fahn, Jeff Foxworthy, Vicki Lawrence, Stephen Root, Jim Cummings, Kath Soucie, Hannah Farr
summary: In Disney's animated follow-up to the 1981 classic, Tod the fox and Copper the hound see their friendship put to the test when Copper finds fame with a howling country-and-western dog band -- and jealousy strikes Tod.

title: Sneakers
cast: Robert Redford, Dan Aykroyd, Ben Kingsley, Mary McDonnell, River Phoenix, Sidney Poitier, David Strathairn, Stephen Tobolowsky, Timothy Busfield
summary: Shadowy government agents blackmail a reformed hacker and his team of security experts into stealing a code-breaking box from a Soviet-funded genius.

title: Incident at Oglala: The Leonard Peltier Story

summary: Narrated by Robert Redford, this provocative documentary chronicles the controversial events surrounding the shooting of two FBI agents on South Dakota's Pine Ridge Reservation in 1975, resulting in the conviction of Sioux activist Leonard Peltier. Featuring reenactments and interviews with key players in the incident, the film offers evidence that the government's prosecution of Peltier was unjust and politically motivated.

title: The Great Gatsby
cast: Robert Redford, Mia Farrow, Bruce Dern, Karen Black, Scott Wilson, Sam Waterston, Lois Chiles, Howard Da Silva, Roberts Blossom, Edward Herrmann
summary: Mysterious millionaire Jay Gatsby is obsessed with Daisy Buchanan in this 1974 film adaptation of F. Scott Fitzgerald's novel. Beyond Gatsby's grasp, Daisy is married to unfaithful Tom, making for a love triangle that ends with broken hearts.

title: Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid
cast: Paul Newman, Robert Redford, Katharine Ross, Strother Martin, Jeff Corey, George Furth, Cloris Leachman, Ted Cassidy, Kenneth Mars, Donnelly Rhodes
summary: Legendary outlaws Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid display their gifts for perfect comedic timing as they pull off heist after heist. To evade a posse, the boys flee to Bolivia, but trouble finds the charming pair of desperadoes wherever they go.

title: Indecent Proposal
cast: Robert Redford, Woody Harrelson, Demi Moore, Billy Bob Thornton, Oliver Platt, Rip Taylor
summary: For one million dollars, a handsome billionaire proposes to Diana that they spend a single night together. Her husband is a cash-strapped architect who could use the cash. Will she do it?

title: The Great Waldo Pepper
cast: Robert Redford, Susan Sarandon, Bo Brundin, Margot Kidder, Bo Svenson, Geoffrey Lewis, Edward Herrmann, Philip Bruns, Roderick Cook, Kelly Jean Peters
summary: Charming stunt pilot Waldo Pepper (Robert Redford) soars through the Midwestern skies in his biplane, seeking the fame he missed out on during World War I -- and the chance to outperform the greatest pilot of all time, German ace Ernst Kessler (Bo Brundin). As the jaded public demands increasingly risky tricks, Waldo and Kessler both leave barnstorming behind and head to Hollywood to film a high-flying war flick.

title: Buck
cast: Buck Brannaman, Robert Redford

The master horseman reveals details of his troubled childhood and his dawning awareness of new ways that humans and horses might work with one another. As Buck learns more about horses, he finds that the ways we communicate with our animal companions offer lessons on how we relate to fellow human beings.

title: Trudell

The documentary includes commentary from Robert Redford, Kris Kristofferson, Sam Shepard, Val Kilmer, Jackson Browne, Bonnie Raitt, Amy Ray of the Indigo Girls and Wilma Mankiller, the first woman principal chief of the Cherokee Nation.

title: This Property Is Condemned
cast: Natalie Wood, Robert Redford, Charles Bronson, Kate Reid, Mary Badham, Alan Baxter, Robert Blake, Dabney Coleman, John Harding, Jon Provost, Ray Hemphill
summary: When railroad official Owen Legate visits a small Depression-era town to shut down its rail yard, he begins a passionate affair with a local girl.

title: All Is Lost
cast: Robert Redford
summary: In this harrowing drama -- which has no dialogue -- a man stranded alone at sea courageously battles a ferocious storm as he struggles to survive.

title: Serial Killing 101
cast: Thomas Haden Church, Justin Urich, Lisa Loeb, Rick Overton, George Murdock, Barbara Niven, Stuart Stone, Raymond O'Connor
summary: A high school student who hopes to live in infamy concocts a scheme to make a willing friend his first victim. But as they read up on serial killers, the two find themselves tracking a murderer in their midst.

title: Another Happy Day
cast: Ellen Barkin, Ezra Miller, Ellen Burstyn, Demi Moore, Thomas Haden Church, Kate Bosworth, George Kennedy, Jeffrey DeMunn, Siobhan Fallon, Diana Scarwid
summary: Upper-crust family dysfunction takes center stage in this drama, which stars Ellen Barkin as a divorcée attending the highbrow wedding of the son she barely knows and trying to hold her own against a family that couches judgment in every smile.

title: Whitewash
cast: Thomas Haden Church, Marc Labrèche, Emanuel Hoss-Desmarais, Vincent Hoss-Desmarais, Geneviève Laroche, Isabelle Nélisse, Anie Pascale
summary: After recklessly killing a pedestrian, a drunken snowplow operator finds himself stranded in the forest -- and courting death in the bitter cold.

title: Mr. Smith Goes to Washington

Zoe Saldana co-stars as a gorgeous alumna.

The all-star cast includes Reese Witherspoon, Stockard Channing, James Garner and Liev Schreiber.

Celebrity voices include Cloris Leachman, Robert Stack and David Letterman.

Lou Antonio (The Steeler and the Pittsburgh Kid) directs this made-for-television drama that features Leachman singing the title song.

When word of this gets out, Ruth's caught in the middle of a tug-of-war between anti-abortion and abortion rights activists who want to use Ruth to get their messages across.

Twenty bloody years later, Tony returns to his high school, where he is able to pass himself off as his own son and enjoy all the glory he missed, including football stardom and hot chicks.

title: The Land Before Time II: The Great Valley Adventure
cast: Scott McAfee, Candace Hutson, Heather Hogan, Jeff Bennett, Rob Paulsen, Linda Gary, Kenneth Mars, John Ingle, Tress MacNeille
summary: Littlefoot and his pals are back in this sequel to animator Don Bluth's opus about warm and caring dinosaurs. Now living in the Great Valley, the pint-size reptiles spot a pair of egg thieves from a secret hideaway they've made. Eager to prove themselves, the dinos track down the missing eggs. But in the process, they open up their valley to evil outsiders and Littlefoot ends up lost in the frightening Great Beyond.

title: Radio Days
cast: Mia Farrow, Julie Kavner, Dianne Wiest, Tony Roberts, Danny Aiello, Jeff Daniels, Diane Keaton, Seth Green, Larry David, Mike Starr, Paul Herman, Don Pardo, Martin Rosenblatt, Helen Miller, Danielle Ferland, Julie Kurnitz, David Warrilow, Kenneth Mars
summary: Told through vignettes, director Woody Allen's Oscar-nominated comedy set in 1940s Brooklyn draws heavily on his youth -- a time when radio was king.

title: The Producers
cast: Zero Mostel, Gene Wilder, Dick Shawn, Kenneth Mars, Lee Meredith, Christopher Hewett, Andréas Voutsinas, Estelle Winwood, Renée Taylor, William Hickey, David Patch
summary: A rapacious but lovable producer hasn't had a hit in years ... until he and his accountant come up with a plot to oversell shares in a surefire flop.

title: Barricade
cast: Eric McCormack, Jody Thompson, Conner Dwelly, Ryan Grantham, Donnelly Rhodes, Dalias Blake
summary: Looking to rebuild the family bond, a father takes his kids to a mountain cabin, only to find they may all be trapped inside with an evil presence.

title: Comic Book Villains
cast: Donal Logue, Cary Elwes, Michael Rapaport, Natasha Lyonne, DJ Qualls, Eileen Brennan, Monet Mazur, Danny Masterson, James Duval, Marshall Bell
summary: Comic book collector Archie is an innocent bystander caught in the rivalry between two stores that explode over a treasure trove of classic comics.

title: The New Adventures of Pippi Longstocking
cast: Tami Erin, David Seaman Jr., Cory Crow, Eileen Brennan, Dennis Dugan, Dianne Hull, George DiCenzo, J.D. Dickinson, Chub Bailly, Dick Van Patten
summary: After pigtailed Pippi washes overboard, she drifts ashore to a seaside village and turns the town upside down with her high jinks and magic powers.

title: Jeepers Creepers
cast: Gina Philips, Justin Long, Jonathan Breck, Patricia Belcher, Eileen Brennan
summary: Bickering siblings get more than they bargained for when they decide to investigate after witnessing a truck driver tossing body bags into a sewer.

title: Paper Moon
cast: Ryan O'Neal, Tatum O'Neal, Madeline Kahn, John Hillerman, P.J. Johnson, Jessie Lee Fulton, Lila Waters, Noble Willingham, Bob Young II
summary: A con man and his precocious "daughter" grift their way across depression-era America in director Peter Bogdanovich's nostalgic look at the 1930s.

title: Won Ton Ton: The Dog Who Saved Hollywood
cast: Bruce Dern, Madeline Kahn, Art Carney, Phil Silvers, Teri Garr, Ron Leibman, Robert Alda, Morey Amsterdam, Army Archerd, Richard Arlen, Billy Barty, Milton Berle, Edgar Bergen, Zsa Zsa Gabor, Rory Calhoun, Walter Pidgeon, Ann Rutherford
summary: When a studio head makes a mongrel dog into a movie star, the pooch's wild success spells opportunity for a would-be starlet and a wannabe producer.

title: Freedom Force
cast: Christopher Lloyd, Sarah Michelle Gellar
summary: To reverse a plot to erase the most famous stories from history, a group of kids and their dog are sent back in time to restore the beloved tales.

title: Dead Before Dawn
cast: Devon Bostick, Martha MacIsaac, Christopher Lloyd, Brandon Jay McLaren, Brittany Allen, Kyle Schmid, Tim Doiron, April Mullen, Kevin McDonald, Ellen Dubin
summary: A horde of zombie demons, or zemons, is unleashed on the world after college kids unwittingly create an evil curse. This curse causes everyone whom they make eye contact with to turn into zemons. Now, they only have 24 hours to reverse the curse.

title: The Addams Family
cast: Anjelica Huston, Raul Julia, Christopher Lloyd, Dan Hedaya, Elizabeth Wilson, Judith Malina, Carel Struycken, Dana Ivey, Paul Benedict, Christina Ricci
summary: Stepping out of the pages of Charles Addams' cartoons and the 1960s television series, the beloved macabre family takes to the big screen in a tale that centers on con artists out to swindle them by introducing a bogus Uncle Fester into their home.

title: Santa Buddies
cast: George Wendt, Christopher Lloyd, Danny Woodburn, Paul Rae, Michael Teigen, Josh Flitter, Quinn Lord, Chris Coppola, Field Cate
summary: When golden retriever pup Budderball gets his name on Santa Paws's naughty list, Santa Paws's son, Puppy Paws, decides to take Budderball under his paw in this family-friendly North Pole adventure.

title: The Adventures of Mickey Matson and the Copperhead Treasure
cast: Derek Brandon, Francesca Derosa, Patrika Darbo, Christopher Lloyd, Lee Arenberg, Ernie Hudson, Frank Drank, Kevin Yon
summary: Unraveling clues left by his late grandfather, teenager Mickey Matson and his friends embark on a perilous journey in search of three magical objects that could change the Civil War's outcome if they fall into the hands of an evil cabal.

title: To Be or Not to Be
cast: Mel Brooks, Anne Bancroft, Tim Matheson, Charles Durning, Christopher Lloyd, José Ferrer, Ronny Graham, Jack Riley, Estelle Reiner, Zale Kessler
summary: Mel Brooks and his real-life spouse, Anne Bancroft, star as impresarios of a Polish acting troupe circa 1939. When the Nazis invade Warsaw, the ensemble gets enmeshed in a subterfuge to prevent the Germans from finding a list of underground fighters. Bancroft scored an Oscar nomination, as did Charles Durning for his supporting performance as a befuddled Nazi colonel in this zesty remake of Ernst Lubitsch's 1942 classic.

title: Who Framed Roger Rabbit
cast: Bob Hoskins, Christopher Lloyd, Joanna Cassidy, Charles Fleischer, Stubby Kaye, Alan Tilvern, Richard Le Parmentier, Lou Hirsch, Betsy Brantley, Kathleen Turner
summary: Director Robert Zemeckis seamlessly mixes live action with animation wizardry in this cinematic groundbreaker featuring Bob Hoskins as gruff gumshoe Eddie Valiant, who agrees to take the case of Roger Rabbit, a zany cartoon star framed for murder.

title: Delhi Safari
cast: Jason Alexander, Cary Elwes, Brad Garrett, Christopher Lloyd, Jane Lynch, Vanessa Williams, Tara Strong, Tom Kenny, Carlos Alazraqui, Troy Baker
summary: Human encroachment is about to send the denizens of a wildlife reserve packing, until an anger-management-guru bear suggests diplomacy. But only one of the animals can break the language barrier: a human-loving, animal-hating parrot named Alex.

title: The Animated Adventures of Tom Sawyer
cast: Ross Malinger, Ryan Slater, Kirsten Dunst, Christopher Lloyd, Jane Mortifee, Blu Mankuma, Garry Chalk, Jay Brazeau
summary: Mark Twain's classic tale gets the animated musical treatment in this family-friendly film that finds Tom Sawyer, Huckleberry Finn and Becky Thatcher cutting loose in a series of riotous, song-filled adventures.

title: Snowmen
cast: Bobby Coleman, Josh Flitter, Ray Liotta, Christopher Lloyd, Bobb'e J. Thompson, Beverley Mitchell, Doug E. Doug, Hunter Clary, Talon G. Ackerman
summary: In this family-friendly drama, a surprising discovery in the snow catapults three small-town boys into the spotlight. Soon the pals hatch a plan to be remembered forever by setting a world record for building snowmen.

title: A Perfect Day
cast: Rob Lowe, Frances Conroy, Paget Brewster, Christopher Lloyd, Jude Ciccolella, Rowena King, Kevin Dunn, Meggie Geisland
summary: After penning a novel based on the death of his wife's father, writer Robert Harlan finds sudden fame and fortune. But when his success makes him lose sight of his family and friends, a mysterious stranger arrives with a wake-up call.

title: Love, Wedding, Marriage
cast: Mandy Moore, Kellan Lutz, James Brolin, Jane Seymour, Jessica Szohr, Michael Weston, Marta Zmuda Trzebiatowska, Richard Reid, Christopher Lloyd, Alexis Denisof
summary: When a newly wedded marriage counselor learns that her seemingly happy parents are serious candidates for divorce, she throws all the rules out the window to repair their fractured relationship.

title: Eight Men Out
cast: John Cusack, Clifton James, Michael Lerner, Christopher Lloyd, John Mahoney, Charlie Sheen, David Strathairn, D.B. Sweeney, Don Harvey, Michael Rooker
summary: John Cusack and D.B. Sweeney star as disgruntled Chicago White Sox players who agree to lose the 1919 World Series for a big payoff.

title: Addams Family Values
cast: Anjelica Huston, Raul Julia, Christopher Lloyd, Joan Cusack, Christina Ricci, Carol Kane, Jimmy Workman, Kaitlyn Hooper, Kristen Hooper, Carel Struycken, David Krumholtz, Christopher Hart, Dana Ivey, Peter MacNicol, Christine Baranski
summary: Siblings Wednesday and Pugsley Addams will stop at nothing to get rid of Pubert, the new baby boy adored by parents Gomez and Morticia.

title: Blood Lake
cast: Shannen Doherty, Jason Brooks, Zack Ward, Christopher Lloyd, Ciara Hanna, Yar Koosha, Fred Stoller, Rachel True, Jeremy Wade, Susie Abromeit
summary: Thousands of starved lamprey eels begin attacking the citizens of a sleepy lake town, leaving the community scrambling to stay alive.

title: Hey Arnold! The Movie
cast: Spencer Klein, Dan Castellaneta, Tress MacNeille, Paul Sorvino, Christopher Lloyd, Jennifer Jason Leigh, Vincent Schiavelli, Maurice LaMarche, Francesca Smith, Jamil Walker Smith
summary: Fourth-grader Arnold and his pal Gerald are forced to come up with a plan when a developer wants to build a huge "mall-plex" in Arnold's neighborhood.

title: Anastasia
cast: Meg Ryan, John Cusack, Kelsey Grammer, Christopher Lloyd, Hank Azaria, Angela Lansbury, Bernadette Peters, Kirsten Dunst
summary: Anya grows up in an orphanage and has no idea that's she's really Anastasia, the long-lost daughter of Russia's last czar.

cast: Michael Ironside, Christopher Lloyd, Katharine Isabelle, Alan C. Peterson, Kyle Schmid, April Mullen, Jesse McCartney, Anthony Ulc, Tim Doiron, Mickey Moon
summary: When a woman awakens in a diner with no idea how she got there, the mystery propels her on a revenge-fueled journey split between two timelines.

title: Coneheads
cast: Dan Aykroyd, Jane Curtin, Michelle Burke, Sinbad, Phil Hartman, Adam Sandler, David Spade, Michael McKean, Jason Alexander, Lisa Jane Persky
summary: An odd alien family with cone-shaped heads, robotlike walks and an appetite for toilet paper tries to blend into a Paramus, N.J., neighborhood.

title: Planes, Trains and Automobiles
cast: Steve Martin, John Candy, Laila Robins, Michael McKean, Kevin Bacon, Dylan Baker, Carol Bruce, Olivia Burnette, Diana Douglas, Martin Ferrero
summary: While trying to get home to his family in Chicago for Thanksgiving, marketing executive Neal Page runs into one disaster after another -- which includes being stuck with insufferable salesman Del Griffith as his unshakable traveling companion.

title: Teaching Mrs. Tingle
cast: Helen Mirren, Marisa Coughlan, Katie Holmes, Jeffrey Tambor, Barry Watson, Liz Stauber, Michael McKean, Molly Ringwald, Vivica A. Fox
summary: Leigh Ann's nasty teacher, Mrs. Tingle, is the one thing that is stopping her from becoming valedictorian. While trying to get Mrs. Tingle to see her way, Leigh Ann gets caught in a misunderstanding that leads to blackmail and possibly worse.

title: The Hunchback of Notre Dame II
cast: Jason Alexander, Jennifer Love Hewitt, Tom Hulce, Paul Kandel, Charles Kimbrough, Kevin Kline, Michael McKean, Demi Moore, Haley Joel Osment, Jane Withers
summary: Disney brings back the all-star voice talents from their 1996 animated feature for this charming new story in which Quasi falls in love with Madellaine, the enchanting assistant to a sinister magician.

title: Cracking Up
cast: Michael Mislove, Fred Willard, Paul Zegler, Steve Bluestein, Harry Shearer, Michael McKean, David L. Lander, Jim Fisher
summary: Inspired funnymen Harry Shearer, Michael McKean and Fred Willard star in this collection of comic sketches that parodies a TV news team as it hustles to cover the aftermath of the Big One -- an earthquake that has California cracking up and sliding into the sea. Combining fake commercials with faux disaster reportage, the film showcases the talents of comedy troupes the Credibility Gap and Ace Trucking Company.

title: The Pass
cast: William Forsythe, James Le Gros, Elizabeth Peña, Jamie Kennedy, Michael McKean, Nancy Allen
summary: After his wife leaves him, a businessman with a compulsive gambling problem travels to Reno, Nev., for some gambling therapy -- which takes a turn when he picks up a psychotic serial killer posing as a hitchhiker.

title: The Producers
cast: Nathan Lane, Matthew Broderick, Uma Thurman, Will Ferrell, Gary Beach, Roger Bart, Michael McKean, David Huddleston, Debra Monk, Andrea Martin
summary: A has-been Broadway producer and a neurotic accountant scheme to raise a ton of money for a production that's sure to be a flop -- a play titled "Springtime for Hitler," penned by a Nazi -- so they can then pocket the extra cash.

title: Never Again
cast: Jeffrey Tambor, Jill Clayburgh, Caroline Aaron, Bill Duke, Sandy Duncan, Michael McKean, Bill Weeden, David Bailey, Caitlin Clarke, Peter Dinklage
summary: After declaring they'll never fall in love again, a mismatched, middle-aged pair meet under the strangest of circumstances -- in a gay bar -- and gradually realize there may still be hope for them. Think of it as When Harry Met Sally for fifty-somethings. Jeffrey Tambor and Jill Clayburgh star in this candid, lighthearted film that looks at the emotional and sexual lives of two single, 54-year-old New Yorkers.

title: Short Circuit 2
cast: Fisher Stevens, Michael McKean, Cynthia Gibb, Jack Weston, Dee McCafferty, David Hemblen, Don Lake, Damon D'Oliveira
summary: In this sequel to the cybernetic comedy, the friendly robot -- going by the name "Johnny" Five -- reunites with his creator, a New York City toymaker.

title: D.A.R.Y.L.
cast: Mary Beth Hurt, Michael McKean, Kathryn Walker, Colleen Camp, Josef Sommer, Ron Frazier, Steve Ryan, David Wohl, Danny Corkill, Amy Linker, Barret Oliver
summary: After escaping from a maximum-security research facility, D.A.R.Y.L. (Data Analyzing Robot Youth Lifeform) is rescued and adopted by the Richardson family. Domestic bliss ensues until D.A.R.Y.L.'s actual "parents," two scientists, come to claim him.

title: My First Mister
cast: Albert Brooks, Leelee Sobieski, Desmond Harrington, Carol Kane, Mary Kay Place, Michael McKean, John Goodman, Pauley Perrette, Rutanya Alda
summary: A neurotic, 49-year-old store owner and his teenage clerk from a dysfunctional family form an unbreakable bond that helps heal their emotional wounds.

title: My Bodyguard
cast: Chris Makepeace, Adam Baldwin, Matt Dillon, Paul Quandt, Hank Salas, Joan Cusack, Dean R. Miller, Tim Reyna, Richard Bradley, Martin Mull
summary: Tormented by bullies, new kid Clifford seeks protection from older student Linderman, a burly loner who's rumored to have killed his own brother.

title: And They're Off...
cast: Sean Astin, Cheri Oteri, Mark Moses, Gigi Rice, Peter Jacobson, Mo Collins, Little JJ, Martin Mull, Kevin Nealon
summary: After years of repeated losses, down-and-out horse trainer Dusty tries to get his life back on the track by adopting a winning strategy. But the only person who can help him win is his needy ex-girlfriend, a diminutive jockey.

title: Far Out Man
cast: Tommy Chong, C. Thomas Howell, Rae Dawn Chong, Martin Mull, Paul Bartel, Judd Nelson, Cheech Marin, Michael Winslow, Paris Chong, Shelby Chong
summary: A trip to a hypnotherapist inspires a middle-aged hippie to set off on a wild adventure-filled cross-country quest in search of the wife and son whom he hasn't seen since the Woodstock era.

title: Jobs
cast: Ashton Kutcher, Dermot Mulroney, Josh Gad, Lukas Haas, J.K. Simmons, Lesley Ann Warren, Ron Eldard, Ahna O'Reilly, Victor Rasuk, John Getz
summary: Ashton Kutcher delivers a tour de force performance as Apple founder Steve Jobs in this biopic that spans three decades of the entrepreneur's life.

title: Peep World
cast: Lewis Black, Ron Rifkin, Rainn Wilson, Taraji P. Henson, Sarah Silverman, Stephen Tobolowsky, Nicholas Hormann, Lesley Ann Warren, Judy Greer, Michael C. Hall
summary: When four siblings gather to celebrate their father's 70th birthday, the proverbial you-know-what hits the fan because one of them has penned a novel populated by characters who strongly resemble his nearest and dearest. How will this dysfunctional family keep it together after everyone has seemingly been hung out to dry? Barry W. Blaustein's ensemble-cast comedy stars Rainn Wilson, Ron Rifkin, Michael C. Hall and Sarah Silverman.

title: A Little Help
cast: Jenna Fischer, Chris O'Donnell, Rob Benedict, Kim Coates, Lesley Ann Warren, Brooke Smith, Aida Turturro, Nadia Dajani, Arden Myrin
summary: After the sudden death of her husband, a Long Island dental hygienist finds herself caught up in a couple of giant lies and begins to feel drawn to her sister's husband as she tries to negotiate life and finances for herself and her 12-year-old son.

title: Going All the Way
cast: Jeremy Davies, Ben Affleck, Amy Locane, Rose McGowan, Rachel Weisz, John Lordan, Bob Swan, Jill Clayburgh, Lesley Ann Warren
summary: Opposites attract when meek, introspective Sonny Burns (Jeremy Davies) and outgoing charmer "Gunner" Casselman (Ben Affleck) form an unlikely friendship in the days following the Korean War. Gunner sets out to show Sonny what he's missing in life -- namely, girls. And Sonny realizes that, besides women, a whole other life lies outside the parochial confines of his small town.

title: The Game of Death
cast: Bruce Lee, Colleen Camp, Dean Jagger, Gig Young, Tai Chung Kim, Biao Yuen, Bob Wall, Kareem Abdul-Jabbar, Mel Novak, Hugh O'Brian
summary: Martial arts icon Bruce Lee made his final film appearance in this action-packed tale of Billy Lo, a champion fighter and movie star who must fake his death to escape and then expose the crime syndicate that wants to control him. When his fiancée, Ann (Colleen Camp), is kidnapped, Billy comes out of hiding and infiltrates the gang's headquarters, a restaurant where Billy engages in one-on-one combat with a number of increasingly deadly opponents.

title: Second to Die
cast: Erika Eleniak, Jerry Kroll, Colleen Camp, John Wesley Shipp, Brooke Davis, Kimberly Rowe, Paul Winfield, Margaret Avery, Jackie O'Brien, Marshall R. Teague
summary: When snagging a rich husband fails to bring her happiness, Sarah Morgan decides he's worth more dead than alive. But her plan hits a snag when she can't collect on his insurance policy and realizes she may have to kill again to cover up her crime.

title: Machete Maidens Unleashed!
cast: Carmen Argenziano, Allan Arkush, John Ashley, Alan Birkinshaw, Judith M. Brown, Andrea Cagan, Colleen Camp, Steve Carver, Leigh Christian, Roger Corman
summary: In the 1970s and '80s, makers of exploitation films loved to shoot in the Philippines, which offered gorgeous scenery, beautiful extras and cheap fun in the sun for the crew. This intriguing documentary examines the real face of Hollywood in Manila. Directors such as Roger Corman and Eddie Romero shot in the Southeast Asian nation, and their movies overflowed with sex, gore and action. Plentiful movie clips and in-depth interviews are featured.

title: Black Moon Rising
cast: Tommy Lee Jones, Linda Hamilton, Richard Jaeckel, Robert Vaughn, Bubba Smith, Lee Ving, Keenan Wynn, William Sanderson, Nick Cassavetes, Dan Shor
summary: Hired by the FBI to pilfer top-secret data from a company, expert burglar Sam follows through on his latest assignment -- but leaves the data behind in an experimental supercar. When the vehicle is stolen, Sam's life depends on getting it back.

title: The Family
cast: Robert De Niro, Michelle Pfeiffer, Tommy Lee Jones, Dianna Agron, John D'Leo, Domenick Lombardozzi, Jimmy Palumbo, Vincent Pastore, Jon Freda
summary: The Manzonis, an infamous mob family, are relocated to Normandy, France, by the witness protection program and have some difficulty fitting in.

title: Men in Black II
cast: Tommy Lee Jones, Will Smith, Rip Torn, Lara Flynn Boyle, Johnny Knoxville, Rosario Dawson, Tony Shalhoub, Patrick Warburton, Jack Kehler, David Cross
summary: Will Smith and Tommy Lee Jones reprise their roles as Jay and Kay, two highly secretive, highly funded and highly unofficial government agents dealing with all things evil and alien -- including "outing" aliens living among us.

title: Double Jeopardy
cast: Tommy Lee Jones, Ashley Judd, Jay Brazeau, Bruce Greenwood, John Maclaren, Ed Evanko, Annabeth Gish
summary: Libby Parsons is arrested for the murder of her husband. While in prison, she finds out that she's been framed. Now, the law of "double jeopardy" -- and the desire to kill her "late" husband for good -- is all she has left.

title: Small Soldiers
cast: Kirsten Dunst, Tommy Lee Jones, Jay Mohr, Gregory Smith, Phil Hartman, Kevin Dunn, Denis Leary, Ernest Borgnine, Frank Langella
summary: The Commando Elite are toy action figures programmed to annihilate another toy group, the Gorgonites. But before the Elite have been tested, the son of a toy store owner opens them, causing the Elite to attack the children playing with them.

title: The Executioner's Song
cast: Tommy Lee Jones, Christine Lahti, Rosanna Arquette, Eli Wallach, Steven Keats, Jordan Clarke, Richard Venture, Jenny Wright, Walter Olkewicz, Michael LeClair
summary: Academy Award winner Tommy Lee Jones took home an Emmy for his starring turn in this made-for-television movie, adapted by acclaimed author-journalist Norman Mailer from his Pulitzer Prize-winning novel. Based on a true story, the compelling drama follows the troubled last days of Gary Gilmore, a career criminal on death row who became the first prisoner executed in the United States after the government's death penalty reinstatement in 1976.

title: April Morning
cast: Chad Lowe, Tommy Lee Jones, Robert Urich, Susan Blakely, Rip Torn, Meredith Salenger, Joan Heney, Nicholas Kilbertus
summary: Based on the penetrating novel by Howard Fast, this coming-of-age tale recounts the adventures of Adam Cooper (Chad Lowe), a teen caught up in the fight between American revolutionary forces and British Redcoats in the crucial Battle of Lexington and Concord. In the midst of the chaos caused by disgruntled colonists, Adam comes to terms with his demanding father, Moses (Tommy Lee Jones), and begins a romance with Ruth (Meredith Salenger).

title: Love Story
cast: Ali MacGraw, Ryan O'Neal, John Marley, Ray Milland, Russell Nype, Sydney Walker, Tommy Lee Jones
summary: Privileged Harvard jock Oliver Barrett IV (Ryan O'Neal) sparks the anger of his steely, demanding father (Ray Milland) by falling in love with and marrying plebeian Radcliffe student Jennifer Cavalleri (Ali MacGraw), prompting his disapproving family to cut off his inheritance. After graduation, Oliver lands a job with a prominent law firm, and the blissful couple has the world by the tail -- until tragedy intervenes.

title: The Missing
cast: Tommy Lee Jones, Cate Blanchett, Evan Rachel Wood, Jenna Boyd, Aaron Eckhart, Val Kilmer, Sergio Calderon, Eric Schweig, Steve Reevis, Jay Tavare
summary: When Maggie Gilkeson's oldest daughter is abducted by a witch doctor turned bandit, Maggie enlists her estranged father's help to find her. But they soon discover that other girls have gone missing -- and that time's running out.

title: Lonesome Dove
cast: Robert Duvall, Tommy Lee Jones, Danny Glover, Diane Lane, Robert Urich, Anjelica Huston, Frederic Forrest, D.B. Sweeney, Ricky Schroder, Chris Cooper
summary: In this Emmy-winning made-for-television movie based on the Larry McMurtry bestseller, two former Texas Rangers leave Texas to settle land in Montana. Their plans are thwarted and helped along by a cast of characters that could only live out West.

title: Emperor
cast: Matthew Fox, Tommy Lee Jones, Eriko Hatsune, Masayoshi Haneda, Colin Moy, Masatoshi Nakamura, Isao Natsuyagi, Masatô Ibu, Takataro Kataoka, Shohei Hino
summary: As World War II ends, Gen. MacArthur oversees Japan's surrender, an act that dispels the nation's centuries-old beliefs about its emperor.

title: The Hunted
cast: Tommy Lee Jones, Benicio Del Toro, Connie Nielsen, Leslie Stefanson, John Finn, José Zúñiga, Ron Canada, Mark Pellegrino, Lonny Chapman, Rex Linn, Jenna Boyd, Eddie Velez
summary: A retired special ops agent is enlisted to track down an assassin with a strange proclivity -- he makes a sport of murdering deer hunters.

title: Batman Forever
cast: Val Kilmer, Chris O'Donnell, Jim Carrey, Tommy Lee Jones, Nicole Kidman, Michael Gough, Pat Hingle, Drew Barrymore, Debi Mazar, Rene Auberjonois
summary: Batman has new villains to vanquish and a new sidekick as millionaire Bruce Wayne goes up against psychotic Two-Face and the Riddler.

title: Christmas Cupid
cast: Chad Michael Murray, Ashley Benson, Ashley Johnson, Christina Milian, Ryan Sypek, Jackee Harry, Burgess Jenkins
summary: Workaholic publicist Sloane Spencer is haunted by the spirit of a newly deceased client, actress Caitlin Quinn, who tries to persuade Sloane to forsake her single-minded life and reunite with a former flame to find true love by Christmas.

title: Snowglobe
cast: Christina Milian, Erin Karpluk, Hilda Doherty, Jason Schombing, James Kot, Josh Cooke, Ennis Esmer, Matt Keeslar, Lorraine Bracco
summary: Angela finds a mystical snow globe that transports her into an idyllic and wintry Christmas wonderland. But when her two worlds unexpectedly collide, Angela must make a choice about what Christmas really means.
